{"questionId":"16443912","questionHtml":"<p>Find the size of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BV</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>VC</mi></math>&nbsp;AND&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the cosine rule on triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BVC</mi></math>&nbsp;for any angle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Recognition must be shown in context either in terms of labelled sides or in side lengths.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>…</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798037</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>(accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math>&nbsp;be the midpoint of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BM</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use sine or cosine in triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BMV</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CMV</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arc</mtext><mi>sin</mi><mtext> </mtext><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>106</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mtext>arc</mtext><mi>cos</mi><mtext> </mtext><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>106</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>399018</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798037</mn><mo>…</mo></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798</mn></math></strong></em>&nbsp;(accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"16443912","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ2.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the size of BVˆC.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}